1
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:06,460
Did it sound like Wen Lang?

2
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:12,530
I practiced for a long time.

3
00:01:15,590 --> 00:01:17,120
What I played for you

4
00:01:19,560 --> 00:01:20,690
was the best played.

5
00:01:30,350 --> 00:01:31,230
Did you like it?

6
00:02:52,180 --> 00:02:57,810
[Sunsets Secrets Regrets]

7
00:02:58,180 --> 00:03:00,580
[Episode 24]

8
00:03:07,030 --> 00:03:08,690
Who's that person next to him?

9
00:03:13,310 --> 00:03:14,110
What's wrong?

10
00:03:14,560 --> 00:03:16,290
Let's watch it again together.

11
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,400
Get Zhou Chuan over here.

12
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:25,430
Coming.

13
00:03:25,430 --> 00:03:26,430
Go, go.

14
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:29,460
It's an interview?

15
00:03:30,190 --> 00:03:30,920
It's a video.

16
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:31,930
Oh, it's a video.

17
00:03:32,310 --> 00:03:33,579
He and Zhao Ping should be friends.

18
00:03:33,579 --> 00:03:34,960
The former Deputy Captain
of the Cheetah Strike Force.

19
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:36,150
In social situations,

20
00:03:36,150 --> 00:03:38,030
you can judge how intimate two people are

21
00:03:38,030 --> 00:03:39,660
based on their distance.

22
00:03:40,310 --> 00:03:42,030
This is often referred to in psychology as

23
00:03:42,030 --> 00:03:43,490
interpersonal distance.

24
00:03:44,030 --> 00:03:45,370
The most handsome guy of our unit,

25
00:03:45,370 --> 00:03:46,840
Captain Zhou Chuan!

26
00:03:46,870 --> 00:03:47,240
Applause!

27
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:48,630
The distance between us right now

28
00:03:48,630 --> 00:03:50,490
shows an intimate relationship.

29
00:03:50,990 --> 00:03:51,840
Further away

30
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:53,430
would be the distance

31
00:03:53,430 --> 00:03:55,490
between acquaintances and friends.

32
00:03:55,870 --> 00:03:56,800
But look,

33
00:03:57,690 --> 00:04:00,750
their distance is so short
throughout the whole video.

34
00:04:01,310 --> 00:04:02,640
Zhao Ping is his friend,

35
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:05,400
but he looks very resistant to him.

36
00:04:06,150 --> 00:04:06,960
You are right.

37
00:04:08,430 --> 00:04:09,800
They are physically very close,

38
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:10,730
but their bodies

39
00:04:10,750 --> 00:04:12,150
are in a defensive state.

40
00:04:12,670 --> 00:04:13,590
His left toe is

41
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:15,190
pointing in the opposite direction,

42
00:04:15,190 --> 00:04:16,850
looking for a chance to leave.

43
00:04:17,019 --> 00:04:18,120
They get along with each other,

44
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:19,560
but there is a barrier between them,

45
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:20,620
or even conflicts.

46
00:04:22,050 --> 00:04:23,450
If we can find this person

47
00:04:23,750 --> 00:04:24,190
and ask about

48
00:04:24,190 --> 00:04:26,450
what happened in the SWAT team back then,

49
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,070
maybe we can get new clues

50
00:04:28,190 --> 00:04:29,270
about the 8/17 Case

51
00:04:29,430 --> 00:04:31,890
and your brother from another perspective.

52
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:41,900
Do you know him?

53
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:47,070
I can't see his face clearly.

54
00:04:47,070 --> 00:04:48,130
This is too blurry.

55
00:04:48,830 --> 00:04:50,040
I need to reconfirm.

56
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,460
I'm hungry, Professor Jiang.

57
00:04:56,630 --> 00:04:59,230
Which cafeteria in your college
has good food?

58
00:05:01,390 --> 00:05:02,790
I have to ask my students.

59
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:03,920
Go ahead.

60
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:05,040
Just right,

61
00:05:05,350 --> 00:05:06,480
I need the restroom.

62
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:13,580
It's on the left when you head out.

63
00:05:36,630 --> 00:05:37,240
Wei.

64
00:05:37,940 --> 00:05:38,560
Hello.

65
00:05:38,810 --> 00:05:39,540
I'm Zhan Wei.

66
00:05:39,830 --> 00:05:40,560
Jin.

67
00:05:41,370 --> 00:05:43,830
You should take
a good look at your marriage.

68
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:47,070
Is Jiang Hansheng with you
because he loves you,

69
00:05:47,070 --> 00:05:48,730
or does he have other motives?

70
00:05:48,950 --> 00:05:50,950
Will your former SWAT colleagues go

71
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:53,040
to Nephew's one-month party?

72
00:05:54,070 --> 00:05:55,720
They are all busy people now.

73
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,270
They might not come.

74
00:05:57,720 --> 00:05:58,430
Why?

75
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:01,620
Did Brother have any enemies before?

76
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:03,900
How could he have any enemies?

77
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:06,170
Why would you suddenly think that?

78
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:20,740
There is a charity fund

79
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:22,360
under He Wu's name.

80
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:25,070
There were

81
00:06:25,750 --> 00:06:28,720
two anonymous donations
of over a million within a year.

82
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:29,390
They end up

83
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:31,270
on his own account,

84
00:06:32,110 --> 00:06:33,909
leaving the source untracable.

85
00:06:35,950 --> 00:06:37,990
Do you want to know Qi's background?

86
00:06:39,690 --> 00:06:40,610
Did he give in?

87
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:42,070
Not yet.

88
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:44,700
He's waiting for the sentencing.

89
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:46,390
The courtyard you found

90
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:48,870
was found by his former lover.

91
00:06:49,270 --> 00:06:50,630
They are from the same hometown—

92
00:06:50,630 --> 00:06:52,950
both from Xiagai Village, Jishui.

93
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:54,040
Qi's

94
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:56,300
original name is Guo Zhengying.

95
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:58,430
His mother died when he was young.

96
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,210
His father
couldn't pay off his usury loans,

97
00:07:01,210 --> 00:07:03,830
so he was beaten to death
by the debt collectors.

98
00:07:03,830 --> 00:07:05,450
Guo Zhengying stabbed two people to death

99
00:07:05,450 --> 00:07:06,710
using a butcher knife.

100
00:07:06,950 --> 00:07:08,310
He then fled to the mountains

101
00:07:08,310 --> 00:07:09,770
and was found a week later.

102
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,980
After being released from prison,

103
00:07:11,980 --> 00:07:13,110
he left his hometown

104
00:07:13,260 --> 00:07:15,320
and went to Jingzhou to make a living.

105
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:17,720
That's it?

106
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:20,180
We are still investigating the rest.

107
00:07:25,140 --> 00:07:25,760
By the way,

108
00:07:26,270 --> 00:07:28,640
two employees of Hengyun Logistics Company

109
00:07:28,640 --> 00:07:29,940
have confessed

110
00:07:30,830 --> 00:07:32,290
to a child abduction case.

111
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:34,270
Those from the Anti-Human Trafficking Department
came this morning.

112
00:07:34,270 --> 00:07:35,510
It is currently confirmed

113
00:07:35,510 --> 00:07:36,600
that the child is 3 years old,

114
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:38,930
and the parents have been looking for her.

115
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:42,570
I've seen that little girl.

116
00:07:43,270 --> 00:07:44,600
She can finally go home.

117
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:46,210
That's good.

118
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:49,510
I can see

119
00:07:49,980 --> 00:07:51,860
you still care about your work.

120
00:07:54,510 --> 00:07:55,800
Of course I do.

121
00:07:56,510 --> 00:07:58,220
It's just that what I can do,

122
00:07:58,240 --> 00:07:59,760
anyone else can do.

123
00:07:59,790 --> 00:08:03,030
And it's more convenient for them to do so
given my identity.

124
00:08:03,030 --> 00:08:05,230
I don't have any special value anymore.

125
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:07,830
Rather than wandering around your team
and causing people annoyance,

126
00:08:07,830 --> 00:08:09,430
it's better for me
to have some self-awareness.

127
00:08:09,430 --> 00:08:11,070
Causing who annoyance?

128
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:14,870
Come in.

129
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:20,370
Are you... feeling better?

130
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:22,750
I'm fine.

131
00:08:23,220 --> 00:08:23,950
What is it?

132
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:24,920
Mentor,

133
00:08:24,940 --> 00:08:27,140
there's an urgent situation
I need to report to you.

134
00:08:27,140 --> 00:08:27,610
Sure.

135
00:08:27,950 --> 00:08:28,630
Director Wang

136
00:08:28,630 --> 00:08:30,640
recently came into contact
with the latest witness

137
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:32,070
in the Huaiguang serial murder cases.

138
00:08:32,070 --> 00:08:32,950
These new clues

139
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:35,440
are directly related
to Qi Yan's background.

140
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:37,080
So I want to go to Jingzhou

141
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:38,620
to look into this clue.

142
00:08:38,789 --> 00:08:40,480
It might give us a new direction.

143
00:08:40,480 --> 00:08:41,030
You can,

144
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:43,120
but you can't go alone.

145
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:44,940
I'll find someone to help you.

146
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:49,520
Professor Jiang will go with me.

147
00:08:49,940 --> 00:08:50,780
Your husband?

148
00:08:52,270 --> 00:08:53,440
Does he have time?

149
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:55,200
This isn't something that can be solved
in a day or two.

150
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:56,730
He applied for a secondment

151
00:08:56,910 --> 00:08:58,040
to focus on the case.

152
00:08:58,100 --> 00:08:58,960
That works too.

153
00:08:59,270 --> 00:09:02,330
After all, Professor Jiang
is familiar with Jingzhou.

154
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:04,820
Besides,
he's in charge of this case anyway.

155
00:09:06,510 --> 00:09:07,370
How about this?

156
00:09:07,550 --> 00:09:09,690
Wan and the others are there too, right?

157
00:09:09,690 --> 00:09:10,600
Once you arrive,

158
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:12,130
contact them immediately.

159
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:13,200
It's best...

160
00:09:14,790 --> 00:09:16,030
Don't worry.

161
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:18,090
Let's wait for the superior's arrangements

162
00:09:18,090 --> 00:09:19,570
for your future work.

163
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:22,120
How can they arrange for anything
if I can't even be reinstated?

164
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:23,320
They'll probably a police station

165
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:24,780
and assign me a cushy spot—

166
00:09:24,870 --> 00:09:28,000
somewhere I can stay comfortably
for the rest of my life.

167
00:09:34,790 --> 00:09:36,120
What are you looking at?

168
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:38,650
Get back to work!

169
00:09:52,070 --> 00:09:53,600
What are you yelling about?

170
00:09:54,910 --> 00:09:56,440
What are you yelling about?

171
00:09:58,270 --> 00:10:01,270
If you have anything on your mind,
just tell me nicely.

172
00:10:12,040 --> 00:10:13,440
I have nothing on my mind.

173
00:10:14,050 --> 00:10:16,510
I'll obey the organization's arrangement.

174
00:10:20,260 --> 00:10:21,690
H-Have a good rest.

175
00:10:22,510 --> 00:10:24,370
Report to me anytime if anything.

176
00:10:31,510 --> 00:10:32,200
It's over.

177
00:10:32,640 --> 00:10:34,500
He has completely lost his faith.

178
00:10:39,030 --> 00:10:39,600
Mentor,

179
00:10:40,060 --> 00:10:41,090
can you help him?

180
00:10:41,550 --> 00:10:42,670
How do I help him?

181
00:10:43,150 --> 00:10:44,120
I can fight for

182
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:45,720
his honor as a policeman.

183
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,540
But as for his love trauma—

184
00:10:48,030 --> 00:10:49,890
is that something I can help with?

185
00:10:51,250 --> 00:10:51,970
Of course.

186
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:53,400
You can't help

187
00:10:53,890 --> 00:10:55,490
at this point of time either.

188
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:58,360
Life's

189
00:10:58,550 --> 00:10:59,550
twists and turns—

190
00:11:00,620 --> 00:11:02,350
he can only face them on his own.

191
00:11:05,510 --> 00:11:07,150
Can he have his lighter back now?

192
00:11:07,150 --> 00:11:07,750
Oh, right.

193
00:11:07,830 --> 00:11:10,630
I would have forgotten
if you hadn't mentioned it.

194
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:13,600
Here.

195
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:16,270
I have some things to say to him.

196
00:11:16,270 --> 00:11:16,910
Okay.

197
00:11:18,190 --> 00:11:19,880
Don't agitate him too much!

198
00:11:25,590 --> 00:11:26,320
Jiang Cheng.

199
00:11:30,150 --> 00:11:30,950
Wait a minute.

200
00:11:31,750 --> 00:11:32,550
Don't come in.

201
00:11:32,750 --> 00:11:33,910
I smell like smoke all over.

202
00:11:33,910 --> 00:11:35,000
You can't stand it.

203
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:37,120
So you know.

204
00:11:37,550 --> 00:11:39,080
Then smoke less from now on.

205
00:11:39,110 --> 00:11:40,440
It would be best to quit.

206
00:11:43,870 --> 00:11:45,330
Is it any of your business?

207
00:11:46,620 --> 00:11:47,580
No, it's not.

208
00:11:55,630 --> 00:11:56,830
Why did you follow me?

209
00:11:57,870 --> 00:11:59,390
I just called Bin.

210
00:12:00,080 --> 00:12:02,240
I asked him to come
to keep you company for a couple of days

211
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:03,480
and have him keep an eye on you.

212
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:04,080
What's your problem?

213
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:06,280
Why do I need someone
to keep an eye on me?

214
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:09,270
I wanted him to bring you

215
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:11,870
your favorite
preserved mustard greens buns.

216
00:12:14,070 --> 00:12:15,350
Fine, fine.

217
00:12:22,150 --> 00:12:23,750
I haven't touched the money

218
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:25,820
you deposited in your debit card.

219
00:12:26,550 --> 00:12:28,880
The PIN has been changed to your birthday.

220
00:12:29,510 --> 00:12:30,910
That money is for you.

221
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:32,200
I can't use it.

222
00:12:38,120 --> 00:12:40,650
If you won't use it,
just donate it somewhere.

223
00:12:43,390 --> 00:12:45,520
Is Jiang Hansheng's family very rich?

224
00:12:47,980 --> 00:12:49,190
If I said that I married him

225
00:12:49,190 --> 00:12:50,760
for his money,

226
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:52,630
would you feel better?

227
00:12:53,630 --> 00:12:55,230
Then I would look down on you.

228
00:12:58,220 --> 00:12:59,200
How is he?

229
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:01,240
I heard that to stop your car,

230
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:03,040
he almost fell off the mountain.

231
00:13:03,500 --> 00:13:05,060
He usually looks ordinary,

232
00:13:05,190 --> 00:13:06,590
but in critical moments,

233
00:13:06,630 --> 00:13:07,360
he's not bad.

234
00:13:07,450 --> 00:13:09,780
This is the first time you've praised him.

235
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,580
Jiang Hansheng is not ordinary.

236
00:13:11,580 --> 00:13:13,500
He used to work in the Provincial Bureau.

237
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:14,380
Tsk.

238
00:13:14,870 --> 00:13:16,600
I don't want to hear about this.

239
00:13:39,150 --> 00:13:39,910
Jin,

240
00:13:40,230 --> 00:13:41,560
are you playing with me?

241
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:55,720
Cheng.

242
00:14:01,360 --> 00:14:02,120
Zhou Jin,

243
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:03,870
you keep following me around—

244
00:14:03,870 --> 00:14:05,870
what exactly do you want to say to me?

245
00:14:08,480 --> 00:14:09,840
I just want to say,

246
00:14:14,020 --> 00:14:15,440
whether I exist or not,

247
00:14:17,480 --> 00:14:19,410
you are still the same Jiang Cheng.

248
00:14:20,270 --> 00:14:21,670
It's because you are good

249
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:23,720
that I liked you.

250
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:26,080
It's because you are confident,

251
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:26,840
brave,

252
00:14:27,270 --> 00:14:28,480
and shining,

253
00:14:29,550 --> 00:14:31,120
that I liked you

254
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:32,550
for many years.

255
00:14:33,750 --> 00:14:35,950
Regardless of whether I like you or not,

256
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:38,030
you are the best person,

257
00:14:38,150 --> 00:14:39,360
the best policeman.

258
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:15,350
Have Bin give the debit card back to me.

259
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:19,010
I'll treat him to a feast for 3 days.

260
00:15:24,550 --> 00:15:26,150
I miss Jin!

261
00:16:09,150 --> 00:16:09,870
Who is it?

262
00:16:09,890 --> 00:16:11,350
Hello, you have a package.

263
00:16:15,780 --> 00:16:16,270
Hello.

264
00:16:16,270 --> 00:16:17,200
Are you Mr. Wang?

265
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:18,270
This is your parcel.

266
00:16:18,270 --> 00:16:18,930
Take a look.

267
00:16:21,450 --> 00:16:22,880
[Hello, Prof Wang.
This is a gift to Professor Jiang.]

268
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:28,670
Prof.

269
00:16:29,320 --> 00:16:31,550
Zhou Jin and I
are going to Jingzhou tonight.

270
00:16:31,550 --> 00:16:33,010
Are you free this evening?

271
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,400
I have some new speculations

272
00:17:00,400 --> 00:17:01,630
regarding Qi Yan, her brother,

273
00:17:01,630 --> 00:17:02,840
and her father

274
00:17:03,080 --> 00:17:05,210
I'd like to talk to you in person about.

275
00:17:54,480 --> 00:17:55,270
Sorry,

276
00:17:55,350 --> 00:17:58,080
the number you dialed
is currently unavailable.

277
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:10,440
Prof?

278
00:18:14,920 --> 00:18:16,520
I'm the security guard here.

279
00:18:16,750 --> 00:18:18,640
I saw you kept calling, so I answered.

280
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:19,200
Well...

281
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:20,480
Something happened to Professor Wang.

282
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:22,610
An ambulance took him to the hospital.

283
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:26,310
Hansheng,

284
00:18:26,400 --> 00:18:27,000
what's wrong?

285
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,600
Something happened to Prof.

286
00:18:28,920 --> 00:18:29,790
What happened?

287
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:30,930
He was attacked.

288
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:32,040
It's serious.

289
00:18:32,110 --> 00:18:33,000
Who did it?

290
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:33,730
I don't know.

291
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:34,830
It could be Qi Yan

292
00:18:34,830 --> 00:18:35,790
or a previous criminal.

293
00:18:35,790 --> 00:18:36,680
Anything is possible.

294
00:18:36,680 --> 00:18:37,480
Hansheng,

295
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:38,400
don't panic.

296
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:39,310
Wait for me at home.

297
00:18:39,310 --> 00:18:40,200
I'll be right back to pick you up.

298
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:41,200
We'll go to Jingzhou.

299
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:41,790
Okay.

300
00:18:41,810 --> 00:18:43,070
Don't scare yourself.

301
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:44,100
Wait for me.

302
00:18:54,680 --> 00:18:55,510
Mr. Wan.

303
00:18:55,880 --> 00:18:57,070
Something happened to Mr. Wang.

304
00:18:57,070 --> 00:18:58,530
Can you go to the Crime Research Lab

305
00:18:58,530 --> 00:19:00,640
to help me
find out the specific situation?

306
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:01,790
Something happened to Director Wang?

307
00:19:01,790 --> 00:19:03,440
It is said that he was attacked.

308
00:19:03,440 --> 00:19:04,830
Okay, I'll ask around.

309
00:19:04,960 --> 00:19:06,960
Okay, I'll be waiting for your news.

310
00:19:15,670 --> 00:19:16,350
Hansheng.

311
00:19:16,590 --> 00:19:17,750
Did you bring your ID card?

312
00:19:17,750 --> 00:19:18,350
Yes.

313
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:20,450
Let's go.

314
00:19:20,450 --> 00:19:21,250
Get in the car.

315
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:34,410
[Mr. Wan]

316
00:19:35,830 --> 00:19:36,680
Mr. Wan,

317
00:19:36,720 --> 00:19:37,550
hold on.

318
00:19:38,590 --> 00:19:39,590
I got the details.

319
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:40,750
The attacker

320
00:19:40,750 --> 00:19:42,790
is a criminal Director Wang
helped catch before.

321
00:19:42,790 --> 00:19:43,700
He just got out of prison.

322
00:19:43,700 --> 00:19:45,590
This time he disguised himself
as a courier

323
00:19:45,590 --> 00:19:46,900
and attacked Director Wang with a hammer.

324
00:19:46,900 --> 00:19:48,350
Fortunately,
the security guard arrived quickly,

325
00:19:48,350 --> 00:19:49,640
so the attacker didn't escape.

326
00:19:49,640 --> 00:19:51,040
How is Director Wang now?

327
00:19:51,200 --> 00:19:52,000
Not very good.

328
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:53,350
He suffered severe head trauma.

329
00:19:53,350 --> 00:19:54,960
Although he was sent
to the hospital in time,

330
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:56,590
he is still in the operating room.

331
00:19:56,590 --> 00:19:57,500
Has the suspect been interrogated?

332
00:19:57,500 --> 00:19:58,160
After the man was caught,

333
00:19:58,160 --> 00:19:59,240
he confessed quickly,

334
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:00,350
saying that
after he was released from prison,

335
00:20:00,350 --> 00:20:01,550
he couldn't reintegrate into society,

336
00:20:01,550 --> 00:20:03,240
so he wanted
to take revenge on Director Wang.

337
00:20:03,240 --> 00:20:04,720
Captain Qian and I
are going to go take a look.

338
00:20:04,720 --> 00:20:06,440
The police have searched his home.

339
00:20:06,440 --> 00:20:07,510
They found nothing.

340
00:20:07,510 --> 00:20:09,240
But at his parents' house,

341
00:20:09,240 --> 00:20:11,040
they found 100,000 yuan in cash.

342
00:20:11,110 --> 00:20:12,510
According to his parents,

343
00:20:12,510 --> 00:20:13,390
this 100,000 yuan

344
00:20:13,390 --> 00:20:15,110
was left for them by their son
for their retirement.

345
00:20:15,110 --> 00:20:16,960
He couldn't reintegrate into society
but had so much money?

346
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:17,880
So,

347
00:20:17,880 --> 00:20:21,340
we can't rule out the possibility
that he was hired by someone.

348
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:23,070
Someone is already following up on it.

349
00:20:23,070 --> 00:20:24,200
You wait for my news.

350
00:20:24,230 --> 00:20:25,550
I'll go to the police station first,

351
00:20:25,550 --> 00:20:27,010
and then go to the hospital
to see Director Wang.

352
00:20:27,010 --> 00:20:27,700
Okay.

353
00:20:27,730 --> 00:20:28,750
Thank you, Mr. Wan.

354
00:20:28,750 --> 00:20:29,960
You're the most welcome.

355
00:20:29,960 --> 00:20:31,240
Be safe on the road.

356
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:33,550
Zhu,

357
00:20:33,550 --> 00:20:34,680
how much longer are we?

358
00:20:34,680 --> 00:20:35,550
About half an hour.

359
00:20:35,550 --> 00:20:36,070
Don't worry,

360
00:20:36,070 --> 00:20:37,930
I'll try to be as fast as possible.

361
00:20:40,480 --> 00:20:41,510
It must be Qi Yan.

362
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:43,510
I can't be wrong.

363
00:20:49,550 --> 00:20:50,510
Don't worry.

364
00:20:50,750 --> 00:20:51,960
Mr. Wang will be fine.

365
00:20:52,460 --> 00:20:54,390
I didn't expect him to attack Prof.

366
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:56,640
It's my negligence.

367
00:20:57,340 --> 00:20:57,970
Hansheng,

368
00:20:58,440 --> 00:20:59,400
don't worry.

369
00:20:59,440 --> 00:21:00,970
Let's see when we get there.

370
00:21:16,590 --> 00:21:17,480
How is Prof?

371
00:21:21,070 --> 00:21:21,790
-Jiang Hansheng!
-What are you doing?

372
00:21:21,790 --> 00:21:23,750
Jiang Hansheng,
how do you have the nerve to come here?

373
00:21:23,750 --> 00:21:24,770
Hubby, let go first.

374
00:21:24,770 --> 00:21:25,750
Let go!

375
00:21:26,200 --> 00:21:26,770
Are you okay?

376
00:21:26,770 --> 00:21:27,500
Calm down.

377
00:21:27,590 --> 00:21:28,680
Dad is still in there.

378
00:21:28,680 --> 00:21:29,440
Calm down?

379
00:21:29,830 --> 00:21:30,510
How can I?

380
00:21:31,370 --> 00:21:33,070
The old man was already retired,

381
00:21:33,070 --> 00:21:34,760
but he went back to work
because of him.

382
00:21:34,760 --> 00:21:35,690
Jiang Hansheng.

383
00:21:36,920 --> 00:21:38,030
You should know better than me

384
00:21:38,030 --> 00:21:39,360
why he's lying in there.

385
00:21:39,720 --> 00:21:41,050
When my mom passed away,

386
00:21:41,510 --> 00:21:43,200
what did you promise her?

387
00:21:44,070 --> 00:21:45,400
I'm telling you, Jiang Hansheng.

388
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:47,060
If anything happens to my dad,

389
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:48,920
you'll pay!

390
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:49,960
I'm sorry.

391
00:21:50,640 --> 00:21:51,070
I'm sorry.

392
00:21:51,070 --> 00:21:52,470
Apologizing is useless!

393
00:21:52,510 --> 00:21:54,840
He is the one lying in there today,
not you!

394
00:21:55,200 --> 00:21:56,110
What are you yelling about?

395
00:21:56,110 --> 00:21:57,350
This is a hospital.

396
00:21:57,480 --> 00:21:58,680
Please be quiet!

397
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:01,110
Hubby, calm down.

398
00:22:02,520 --> 00:22:03,920
I'm going out for a smoke.

399
00:22:07,400 --> 00:22:08,270
I'm sorry.

400
00:22:08,990 --> 00:22:11,450
My husband is just too worried
about his dad,

401
00:22:11,500 --> 00:22:12,780
so he spoke out of turn.

402
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:14,960
We actually know

403
00:22:15,770 --> 00:22:17,500
this has nothing to do with you.

404
00:22:21,640 --> 00:22:22,440
Hansheng.

405
00:22:23,070 --> 00:22:24,400
It's good that you came.

406
00:22:25,510 --> 00:22:26,640
He'll be very happy to see you

407
00:22:26,640 --> 00:22:27,750
when he wakes up.

408
00:22:31,720 --> 00:22:32,400
Thank you.

409
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:34,550
How is

410
00:22:35,590 --> 00:22:36,680
Mr. Wang doing now?

411
00:22:39,640 --> 00:22:40,480
I don't know.

412
00:22:42,110 --> 00:22:43,370
He hasn't woken up yet.

413
00:22:45,510 --> 00:22:46,560
It'd be a hard blow

414
00:22:47,550 --> 00:22:49,750
for someone his age to be hit by a hammer.

415
00:22:53,750 --> 00:22:54,550
You guys take a seat first.

416
00:22:54,550 --> 00:22:56,080
I'll go check on my husband.

417
00:23:39,480 --> 00:23:41,210
Do you want to sleep for a while?

418
00:23:44,160 --> 00:23:45,020
I'm not sleepy.

419
00:23:47,920 --> 00:23:48,780
Are you hungry?

420
00:23:49,920 --> 00:23:51,520
Do you want something to eat?

421
00:23:52,830 --> 00:23:53,790
I can buy you

422
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:56,160
some wontons

423
00:23:56,960 --> 00:23:57,960
and beef noodles.

424
00:23:59,160 --> 00:23:59,820
How's that?

425
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:07,800
Last time I went to Prof's house,

426
00:24:09,110 --> 00:24:10,970
he cooked a bowl of noodles for me.

427
00:24:13,270 --> 00:24:14,840
He was perfectly fine then.

428
00:24:22,880 --> 00:24:23,920
He'll be fine.

429
00:24:26,310 --> 00:24:27,920
Mr. Wang will recover.

430
00:24:44,240 --> 00:24:44,830
Zhou Jin.

431
00:24:49,390 --> 00:24:51,390
I think I did something wrong again.

432
00:24:53,550 --> 00:24:54,270
No.

433
00:24:55,440 --> 00:24:57,100
You didn't do anything wrong.

434
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:57,920
Really.

435
00:25:00,680 --> 00:25:02,280
It has nothing to do with you.

436
00:25:05,070 --> 00:25:06,270
It's not your fault.

437
00:25:39,510 --> 00:25:40,770
My dad wants to see you.

438
00:25:43,590 --> 00:25:44,080
Go ahead.

439
00:25:44,080 --> 00:25:45,340
I'll wait for you here.

440
00:26:22,830 --> 00:26:23,550
Prof.

441
00:26:29,240 --> 00:26:29,890
Prof.

442
00:26:42,290 --> 00:26:43,570
Pup.

443
00:26:45,200 --> 00:26:46,440
Don't cry.

444
00:26:51,610 --> 00:26:52,920
Don't be impulsive.

445
00:26:55,410 --> 00:26:57,710
Think about Zhou.

446
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:03,350
The guy who hit me

447
00:27:04,960 --> 00:27:06,960
said he was delivering a gift

448
00:27:07,770 --> 00:27:10,090
to me for someone else.

449
00:27:14,720 --> 00:27:16,590
There's a mastermind behind this.

450
00:27:16,590 --> 00:27:17,920
Do you know who?

451
00:27:20,790 --> 00:27:21,880
It's Qi Yan.

452
00:27:23,160 --> 00:27:24,680
He

453
00:27:27,160 --> 00:27:28,810
wants to take revenge on you.

454
00:27:30,680 --> 00:27:32,640
Be careful.

455
00:27:34,960 --> 00:27:36,400
Be careful.

456
00:27:49,270 --> 00:27:50,170
Hansheng.

457
00:27:53,000 --> 00:27:53,920
Hansheng.

458
00:27:56,480 --> 00:27:58,550
My good student,

459
00:28:00,500 --> 00:28:02,390
my good friend.

460
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:06,590
I know what you're thinking.

461
00:28:12,480 --> 00:28:14,680
Don't let hatred

462
00:28:16,110 --> 00:28:18,200
blind you.

463
00:28:22,160 --> 00:28:23,030
Professor.

464
00:28:25,240 --> 00:28:26,720
It's my fault.

465
00:28:28,110 --> 00:28:29,790
You were dragged into this.

466
00:28:32,590 --> 00:28:35,110
It is your fault.

467
00:28:37,830 --> 00:28:39,030
So

468
00:28:41,310 --> 00:28:44,790
you have to take care of me in my old age
and see me off.

469
00:29:07,750 --> 00:29:09,070
I'm tired.

470
00:29:10,920 --> 00:29:12,780
I can't keep my eyes open anymore.

471
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:26,200
Officer Jiang.

472
00:30:28,960 --> 00:30:30,120
Do you feel it?

473
00:30:30,920 --> 00:30:32,830
You can't save anyone.

474
00:30:37,590 --> 00:30:38,440
Don't touch her!

475
00:30:38,440 --> 00:30:40,040
Death is actually not scary.

476
00:30:41,350 --> 00:30:43,640
Death is the true beginning

477
00:30:45,650 --> 00:30:47,170
It brings new life.

478
00:31:22,730 --> 00:31:23,490
Hansheng.

479
00:31:24,350 --> 00:31:25,110
How is he?

480
00:31:26,440 --> 00:31:27,200
It's fine.

481
00:31:27,720 --> 00:31:28,720
He'll get better.

482
00:31:29,830 --> 00:31:31,560
I'm going to go see the attacker

483
00:31:31,610 --> 00:31:33,140
and ask him a few questions.

484
00:31:33,350 --> 00:31:35,270
I'll have Mentor
contact the police station.

485
00:31:35,270 --> 00:31:35,830
No need.

486
00:31:37,250 --> 00:31:38,700
Jingzhou is my home turf.

487
00:31:43,160 --> 00:31:44,440
I picked it up.

488
00:31:44,850 --> 00:31:46,450
How many times have I said it?

489
00:31:46,550 --> 00:31:48,210
100,000 is not a small amount.

490
00:31:49,960 --> 00:31:51,730
Did you give this sum to your parents?

491
00:31:51,730 --> 00:31:53,410
No, I spent it.

492
00:31:54,030 --> 00:31:56,000
I bought alcohol and cigarettes.

493
00:31:56,160 --> 00:31:57,200
I bought food too.

494
00:31:57,200 --> 00:31:58,070
Stop talking nonsense.

495
00:31:58,070 --> 00:31:59,420
100,000 is not a small amount.

496
00:31:59,420 --> 00:32:00,750
Can it be spent that fast?

497
00:32:00,750 --> 00:32:02,830
How would I know? I'm a fast spender.

498
00:32:03,280 --> 00:32:05,290
I open 10 bottles of alcohol at a time.

499
00:32:05,290 --> 00:32:06,030
Makes sense, right?

500
00:32:06,030 --> 00:32:06,240
And after that

501
00:32:06,240 --> 00:32:09,200
I went to eat barbecue with the guys.

502
00:32:09,220 --> 00:32:10,790
I also have to...

503
00:32:10,820 --> 00:32:12,170
Well...

504
00:32:12,510 --> 00:32:14,110
Stop messing around with me.

505
00:32:15,070 --> 00:32:16,550
Who's messing around?

506
00:32:16,550 --> 00:32:18,340
I'm talking to you seriously.

507
00:32:20,390 --> 00:32:22,240
I just don't know.

508
00:32:22,270 --> 00:32:23,720
I don't care what you say.

509
00:32:24,510 --> 00:32:26,350
Sentence me if you want, okay?

510
00:32:28,080 --> 00:32:29,410
Are you guys done or not?

511
00:32:30,350 --> 00:32:31,310
Hurry up!

512
00:32:31,720 --> 00:32:33,310
If you can't get an answer, stop asking!

513
00:32:33,310 --> 00:32:35,240
I'm telling you, I just don't know!

514
00:32:35,920 --> 00:32:38,120
Why don't you get someone else to ask me?

515
00:32:38,160 --> 00:32:39,030
Hansheng.

516
00:32:40,880 --> 00:32:41,750
I'll do it.

517
00:33:01,160 --> 00:33:02,290
Someone new to interrogate me?

518
00:33:02,290 --> 00:33:02,770
Okay.

519
00:33:02,880 --> 00:33:03,920
You ask.

520
00:33:03,920 --> 00:33:04,750
Go on.

521
00:33:05,270 --> 00:33:05,920
Shi Qiang.

522
00:33:06,770 --> 00:33:08,230
I'll ask you one last time.

523
00:33:08,350 --> 00:33:10,240
Where did this 100,000 yuan come from?

524
00:33:10,240 --> 00:33:11,400
I don't know.

525
00:33:13,070 --> 00:33:14,160
I picked it up.

526
00:33:15,030 --> 00:33:16,600
I forgot when I picked it up.

527
00:33:16,710 --> 00:33:18,040
Where did you pick it up?

528
00:33:19,250 --> 00:33:20,450
Where did I pick it up?

529
00:33:22,150 --> 00:33:22,840
I forgot.

530
00:33:28,680 --> 00:33:29,830
You guys draft

531
00:33:30,270 --> 00:33:31,600
what questions you ask?

532
00:33:34,640 --> 00:33:35,370
Keep asking.

533
00:33:38,450 --> 00:33:39,170
Go ahead.

534
00:33:46,780 --> 00:33:47,980
What's going on here?

535
00:33:48,990 --> 00:33:49,830
You got someone new,
but they're not saying anything?

536
00:33:49,830 --> 00:33:51,360
What's the meaning of this?

537
00:33:52,400 --> 00:33:53,610
If you're not going to ask,
get someone new.

538
00:33:53,610 --> 00:33:54,540
Get someone new.

539
00:33:54,790 --> 00:33:56,920
Get someone who speaks.

540
00:34:07,700 --> 00:34:08,710
Someone new?

541
00:34:08,840 --> 00:34:09,440
Okay.

542
00:34:10,060 --> 00:34:10,870
Hurry.

543
00:34:11,560 --> 00:34:12,170
Come on.

544
00:34:16,510 --> 00:34:17,070
Let's go.

545
00:34:20,880 --> 00:34:22,400
Speak!

546
00:34:22,400 --> 00:34:24,130
Why aren't you talking either?

547
00:34:25,280 --> 00:34:26,610
Are you playing with me?

548
00:34:27,440 --> 00:34:28,770
Are you playing with me?

549
00:34:34,840 --> 00:34:36,239
If you don't talk, I will.

550
00:34:37,190 --> 00:34:38,670
Name: Shi Qiang.

551
00:34:38,760 --> 00:34:39,840
Age: 32.

552
00:34:39,920 --> 00:34:40,800
Gender: Male.

553
00:34:41,159 --> 00:34:42,380
Where did the 100,000 yuan come from?

554
00:34:42,380 --> 00:34:43,110
I don't know.

555
00:34:43,120 --> 00:34:45,040
I picked it up. Where did you pick it up?

556
00:34:45,040 --> 00:34:45,690
I forgot.

557
00:34:48,190 --> 00:34:49,210
Any other questions? Ask away.

558
00:34:49,210 --> 00:34:50,670
Come on, change the topic.

559
00:34:53,110 --> 00:34:54,190
Ask!

560
00:35:02,300 --> 00:35:03,480
You're back, officer.

561
00:35:03,480 --> 00:35:04,440
Come.

562
00:35:04,460 --> 00:35:05,670
Is it time to eat?

563
00:35:05,700 --> 00:35:06,940
Shouldn't we eat?

564
00:35:06,960 --> 00:35:09,890
Officers, I've been starving for 5 hours.

565
00:35:10,020 --> 00:35:10,870
Are you guys

566
00:35:10,890 --> 00:35:13,750
interrogating me
like this without giving me food?

567
00:35:14,340 --> 00:35:16,180
Right. Open it.

568
00:35:16,850 --> 00:35:18,510
How does it taste? Is it sweet?

569
00:35:18,510 --> 00:35:19,460
I need to eat something sweet now.

570
00:35:19,460 --> 00:35:21,660
I'm low on blood sugar, I'm telling you.

571
00:35:23,990 --> 00:35:25,150
Give me a piece.

572
00:35:27,940 --> 00:35:29,470
Don't just eat it yourself!

573
00:35:29,960 --> 00:35:31,520
Give me a piece!

574
00:35:32,310 --> 00:35:33,670
It's been 5 hours!

575
00:35:34,760 --> 00:35:36,590
Are you just ignoring me?

576
00:35:38,350 --> 00:35:39,680
Can I have a sip of water?

577
00:35:40,660 --> 00:35:41,990
Can I have a sip of water?

578
00:35:42,070 --> 00:35:45,190
My throat is dry. It's smoking.

579
00:36:14,400 --> 00:36:15,150
I know you.

580
00:36:16,630 --> 00:36:17,440
Mr. Jiang.

581
00:36:17,440 --> 00:36:18,500
I'm talking to you.

582
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:20,800
I know you.

583
00:36:30,450 --> 00:36:32,380
How do you know my surname is Jiang?

584
00:36:33,130 --> 00:36:34,060
You're talking.

585
00:36:34,440 --> 00:36:35,370
You're talking!

586
00:36:36,100 --> 00:36:38,030
It's none of your business how I know you.

587
00:36:38,030 --> 00:36:38,760
I also know that old man

588
00:36:38,760 --> 00:36:40,220
is your teacher, isn't he?

589
00:36:40,670 --> 00:36:43,000
That's why they say
old people are useless.

590
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:44,710
I just hit him with a hammer...

591
00:36:47,700 --> 00:36:48,960
And he was done for.

592
00:36:49,070 --> 00:36:51,130
Blood splattered all over the floor.

593
00:36:51,530 --> 00:36:52,930
Too bad you didn't see it.

594
00:36:54,400 --> 00:36:57,260
The person who hired you
told you to say that, right?

595
00:37:02,920 --> 00:37:04,930
Let me think what else he taught you.

596
00:37:16,240 --> 00:37:17,280
He also told you

597
00:37:19,070 --> 00:37:20,600
that after you were caught,

598
00:37:21,320 --> 00:37:22,360
you'd meet a man

599
00:37:23,400 --> 00:37:24,660
named Jiang Hansheng,

600
00:37:25,190 --> 00:37:26,840
a student of Wang Pengze.

601
00:37:27,950 --> 00:37:29,680
But you don't need to be afraid.

602
00:37:30,510 --> 00:37:32,750
You just need to provoke him
using his teacher,

603
00:37:32,750 --> 00:37:34,460
and he'll be led by the nose.

604
00:37:35,210 --> 00:37:37,140
The more exaggerated, the better.

605
00:37:39,590 --> 00:37:41,520
Given this person's personality,

606
00:37:41,630 --> 00:37:43,230
he would also mock me.

607
00:37:45,030 --> 00:37:45,890
He would say...

608
00:37:47,840 --> 00:37:50,480
Jiang Hansheng is a pretentious person.

609
00:37:50,960 --> 00:37:52,420
He claims to be righteous,

610
00:37:52,920 --> 00:37:54,920
but he's actually easy to deal with.

611
00:38:01,110 --> 00:38:02,640
Looks like I guessed right.

612
00:38:06,060 --> 00:38:07,150
What a pity.

613
00:38:08,030 --> 00:38:09,360
Five years have passed,

614
00:38:09,630 --> 00:38:11,290
and he hasn't improved at all.

615
00:38:12,400 --> 00:38:13,400
But Shi Qiang,

616
00:38:14,230 --> 00:38:16,880
do you know why
he only dares to hire a murderer?

617
00:38:18,440 --> 00:38:19,290
Why?

618
00:38:22,180 --> 00:38:24,710
Because he doesn't dare
to fight me directly.

619
00:38:25,080 --> 00:38:27,020
Something even he doesn't dare to do—

620
00:38:27,020 --> 00:38:27,950
how would you?

621
00:38:29,400 --> 00:38:29,880
Honestly speaking,

622
00:38:29,880 --> 00:38:31,280
I'm not interested in

623
00:38:31,280 --> 00:38:33,340
in where your 100,000 yuan came from.

624
00:38:33,600 --> 00:38:35,600
But as for what you did to my teacher,

625
00:38:36,650 --> 00:38:38,850
that's a score I have to settle with you.

626
00:38:40,670 --> 00:38:41,930
How will you settle it?

627
00:38:45,440 --> 00:38:46,440
What do you mean?

628
00:38:47,710 --> 00:38:49,030
I heard you are known as

629
00:38:49,030 --> 00:38:51,230
a very filial son back in your hometown.

630
00:38:52,880 --> 00:38:54,280
The 100,000 you made

631
00:38:55,760 --> 00:38:57,230
from attacking my teacher

632
00:38:58,150 --> 00:38:59,750
was all left to your parents.

633
00:39:00,010 --> 00:39:00,900
So what?

634
00:39:03,510 --> 00:39:04,760
Being filial is good,

635
00:39:05,670 --> 00:39:07,200
but you're just too stupid.

636
00:39:09,150 --> 00:39:10,880
You dropped out of junior high,

637
00:39:11,230 --> 00:39:12,510
so it's understandable

638
00:39:12,510 --> 00:39:13,770
you don't know the law.

639
00:39:14,300 --> 00:39:15,700
But I guarantee you,

640
00:39:16,320 --> 00:39:17,920
your parents won't see a dime

641
00:39:18,000 --> 00:39:19,960
of that 100,000.

642
00:39:20,490 --> 00:39:21,440
What do you mean?

643
00:39:24,630 --> 00:39:25,670
There's no need to get so agitated

644
00:39:25,670 --> 00:39:26,710
about your parents'

645
00:39:26,710 --> 00:39:28,370
miserable life in the future.

646
00:39:29,450 --> 00:39:30,780
You didn't take this job

647
00:39:31,290 --> 00:39:32,680
for them anyway.

648
00:39:37,640 --> 00:39:38,950
Your real purpose

649
00:39:39,690 --> 00:39:41,000
is to go back to prison.

650
00:39:43,760 --> 00:39:45,290
You were jailed for murder.

651
00:39:45,880 --> 00:39:47,510
You were seen as ruthless in jail

652
00:39:47,510 --> 00:39:49,310
and no one dared to mess with you.

653
00:39:49,500 --> 00:39:51,100
But it's different out here.

654
00:39:52,190 --> 00:39:53,790
This is a civilized society.

655
00:39:55,190 --> 00:39:56,750
There's no room for scum.

656
00:40:16,640 --> 00:40:17,410
Hello? Wei?

657
00:40:17,760 --> 00:40:18,590
Jin.

658
00:40:18,650 --> 00:40:20,050
I'm not trying to nag you,

659
00:40:20,070 --> 00:40:21,000
but why didn't you let me know

660
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:22,320
you're in Jingzhou?

661
00:40:22,760 --> 00:40:23,920
I came in a hurry.

662
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:24,930
How did you know?

663
00:40:25,400 --> 00:40:28,060
I'm right at the entrance
of the police station.

664
00:40:28,650 --> 00:40:29,980
I passed by after work.

665
00:40:30,190 --> 00:40:31,510
You come out. I won't go in.

666
00:40:31,510 --> 00:40:32,960
Going in means all sorts of small talk.

667
00:40:32,960 --> 00:40:34,220
It's too troublesome.

668
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:34,960
Okay.

669
00:40:34,960 --> 00:40:35,920
Give me a second.

670
00:40:36,760 --> 00:40:38,360
Is Professor Jiang with you?

671
00:40:40,400 --> 00:40:42,800
It's not very convenient
for him right now.

672
00:40:44,230 --> 00:40:44,940
That's fine.

673
00:40:44,940 --> 00:40:46,140
I just came to see you.

674
00:40:46,440 --> 00:40:46,920
Okay.

675
00:40:47,190 --> 00:40:47,920
Wait for me.

676
00:40:47,920 --> 00:40:48,920
I'll be right out.

677
00:40:49,440 --> 00:40:49,920
Okay.

678
00:40:58,760 --> 00:40:59,400
Wei.

679
00:41:02,440 --> 00:41:02,960
Here.

680
00:41:06,800 --> 00:41:07,660
Fried chicken!

681
00:41:07,880 --> 00:41:08,400
Let's go.

682
00:41:08,400 --> 00:41:09,460
Let's eat by my car.

683
00:41:09,480 --> 00:41:11,070
Where did you park?

684
00:41:11,070 --> 00:41:12,320
Just over there, not far.

685
00:41:12,320 --> 00:41:14,050
There was no place to park here.

686
00:41:14,880 --> 00:41:16,080
There's milk tea too.

687
00:41:17,480 --> 00:41:18,710
Jasmine, 50% sugar.

688
00:41:21,550 --> 00:41:23,350
I haven't had milk tea in so long.

689
00:41:26,230 --> 00:41:26,880
Drink it.

690
00:41:26,990 --> 00:41:27,850
It's still hot.

691
00:41:30,920 --> 00:41:31,480
Drink up.

692
00:41:33,800 --> 00:41:34,510
Let's go.

693
00:41:37,190 --> 00:41:40,120
Director Wang's matter
has spread all over the Provincial Bureau.

694
00:41:40,120 --> 00:41:41,160
How is he doing?

695
00:41:41,190 --> 00:41:43,050
I heard he suffered a head injury.

696
00:41:43,710 --> 00:41:44,840
It's quite serious.

697
00:41:45,070 --> 00:41:47,070
He was in the op room the whole night.

698
00:41:47,280 --> 00:41:48,630
Is he conscious now?

699
00:41:53,190 --> 00:41:54,760
I'm not really sure about that.

700
00:41:54,760 --> 00:41:56,690
Because I haven't seen him either.

701
00:41:58,670 --> 00:42:00,330
What did Professor Jiang say?

702
00:42:01,770 --> 00:42:02,690
About what?

703
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:07,260
Director Wang's attack
should be related to the 8/17 Case.

704
00:42:07,440 --> 00:42:08,960
Did he find out

705
00:42:09,020 --> 00:42:09,860
any new clues?

706
00:42:12,880 --> 00:42:13,940
He interrogating.

707
00:42:14,370 --> 00:42:16,240
The attacker is tight-lipped.

708
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:21,110
Still eating?

709
00:42:21,510 --> 00:42:23,550
Aren't you leaving some
for Professor Jiang?

710
00:42:23,550 --> 00:42:24,820
It won't taste good when it's cold.

711
00:42:24,820 --> 00:42:26,820
Besides, he doesn't eat spicy food.

712
00:42:36,360 --> 00:42:36,840
Wei.

713
00:42:37,710 --> 00:42:39,210
I want to ask you something.

714
00:42:39,210 --> 00:42:39,740
Go ahead.

715
00:42:41,280 --> 00:42:42,480
Do you know Zhao Ping?

716
00:42:43,000 --> 00:42:44,150
Zhao Ping?

717
00:42:48,190 --> 00:42:49,630
Not long ago,

718
00:42:49,630 --> 00:42:51,800
we found a problematic colleague
in our team

719
00:42:51,800 --> 00:42:52,730
named Zhao Ping.

720
00:42:52,840 --> 00:42:54,100
How is he problematic?

721
00:42:55,480 --> 00:42:57,320
Passing intel to a criminal gang.

722
00:42:57,320 --> 00:42:58,190
That serious?

723
00:42:58,400 --> 00:43:00,210
He used to be in the SWAT team too.

724
00:43:00,400 --> 00:43:02,200
So I wanted to ask if you know him.

725
00:43:02,920 --> 00:43:03,800
I don't.
